oc:kn_02a9e38f a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating onboarding content and interactions" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Show, don't tell. Demonstrate with working examples and real functionality, not descriptions or separate tutorial modes." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Users learn by doing — interactive onboarding produces significantly higher comprehension and retention than passive reading." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_0c80ee6a a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When deciding when to introduce features" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Teach features when users need them (contextual), not upfront (ceremonial). Use empty states as onboarding opportunities." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Contextual discovery reduces cognitive load and increases relevance — users remember what they learn when they need it." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_1933f800 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing empty states" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Every empty state must answer three questions: What will be here? Why does it matter? How do I get started? Plus visual interest and contextual help." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Empty states are prime onboarding real estate — they turn dead space into guidance moments that drive activation." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_2bcb2b18 a oc:Idempotency,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When implementing onboarding state persistence" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Onboarding must be idempotent from the user's perspective — returning users should never see initial onboarding again. Track state per user." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Re-showing onboarding to returning users breaks trust and wastes time." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_4539d229 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing any onboarding flow" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Onboarding should get users to value as quickly as possible, not teach everything possible. Front-load the 20% that delivers 80% of value." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Time to value is the single most important onboarding metric — users who reach their 'aha moment' fast are far more likely to retain." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_534e14dd a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:WorkflowStrategy ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing guided tours and walkthroughs" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Keep guided tours to 3-7 steps max, focus on workflow not features, and always make them replayable from a help menu." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Short, workflow-focused tours maintain engagement. Replayability ensures returning users can access help on demand." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_80599793 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When implementing onboarding state tracking" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never show the same tooltip or onboarding step twice. Track completion and respect dismissals using localStorage or similar persistence." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Repeated onboarding is annoying and signals disrespect for the user's time and prior actions." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_8b59ac72 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before starting any onboarding design work" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Must invoke /frontend-design first to load design principles and the Context Gathering Protocol. If no design context exists, must run /teach-impeccable first." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Onboarding design builds on foundational design principles and requires project-specific design context to be effective." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_9a345477 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PreFlightCheck ;
    oc:appliesToContext "At the start of every onboarding design task" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Before designing, gather: the 'aha moment' you want users to reach, users' experience level, and existing design context." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Without knowing the target value moment and audience, onboarding design becomes generic and ineffective." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_cf835d92 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing initial product onboarding" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never force users through long onboarding before they can use the product. Always provide a visible 'Skip' option and don't block access." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Blocking access frustrates experienced users and increases drop-off. Optional onboarding respects user autonomy and intelligence." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

